# Tailwind CSS Rules

## Tailwind v4 Setup
- Use Tailwind v4 CSS-first conventions already defined in `src/styles/globals.css`.
- Keep design tokens and theme variables centralized in `globals.css`.
- Keep PostCSS integration consistent with `@tailwindcss/postcss`.

## Styling Strategy
- Prefer utility classes in JSX over new ad-hoc CSS files.
- Use `@apply` only for repeated style groups that improve readability.
- Keep custom CSS minimal and colocated with global token/theme concerns.
- Use `cn`/merge utilities for conditional class composition.

## Design System And Components
- Reuse `components/ui` (shadcn) primitives first.
- Add shared, app-opinionated variants in `components/shared` when reuse spans features.
- Keep feature-specific visual tweaks inside feature components.
- Keep variant naming consistent across similar components.

## Theming And Accessibility
- Use semantic tokens (`--background`, `--foreground`, `--primary`, etc.) instead of raw colors in components.
- Maintain dark-mode compatibility via the existing `.dark` token strategy.
- Ensure contrast and focus-visible states for interactive controls.

## Responsive And Performance
- Follow mobile-first utility usage.
- Prefer layout primitives (`flex`, `grid`, gap utilities) over custom layout CSS.
- Avoid oversized class duplication; extract reusable patterns only when repeated.